translate ru strings:

    old "Just as they had been instructed, they set out early the next day."
    new "Just as they had been instructed, they set out early the next day."

    old "The Mythran soldiers had looked on with surprise as the mercenary company had rallied the wagons and set out past the great city gates of Bagrad."
    new "The Mythran soldiers had looked on with surprise as the mercenary company had rallied the wagons and set out past the great city gates of Bagrad."

    old "They had looked on with even greater surprise when they saw the mercenaries leave, not through the western gates for Lethram, but the long abandoned eastern gates to nowhere."
    new "They had looked on with even greater surprise when they saw the mercenaries leave, not through the western gates for Lethram, but the long abandoned eastern gates to nowhere."

    old "Some warnings, some jeers, some taunts. Sarah heard them hurl it all at them."
    new "Some warnings, some jeers, some taunts. Sarah heard them hurl it all at them."

    old "Mad, that's what they called them above all."
    new "Mad, that's what they called them above all."

    old "But Vaelen's men were above all loyal to their leader."
    new "But Vaelen's men were above all loyal to their leader."

    old "He had seen them through more than a few encounters that at first had appeared mad, and he had always guided them to victory."
    new "He had seen them through more than a few encounters that at first had appeared mad, and he had always guided them to victory."

    old "So, they thought, what of it then? One more mad gamble to add to the others."
    new "So, they thought, what of it then? One more mad gamble to add to the others."

    old "Sarah rode one of the many wagons, near the front but now with Vaelen."
    new "Sarah rode one of the many wagons, near the front but now with Vaelen."

    old "He had offered her, but Sarah had politely refused."
    new "He had offered her, but Sarah had politely refused."

    old "She preferred to ride with the other soldiers, her own officers."
    new "She preferred to ride with the other soldiers, her own officers."

    old "Some commanders had a habit of isolating themselves, existing only in a reality made up out of papers and reports drafted by their underlings."
    new "Some commanders had a habit of isolating themselves, existing only in a reality made up out of papers and reports drafted by their underlings."

    old "Sarah was eager to avoid such a fate."
    new "Sarah was eager to avoid such a fate."

    old "She had already fooled herself once, believing that being born to a safe life meant she would remain safe."
    new "She had already fooled herself once, believing that being born to a safe life meant she would remain safe."

    old "But deep down, Sarah also knew there was more to it."
    new "But deep down, Sarah also knew there was more to it."

    old "Vaelen's behavior ever since Bagrad had troubled her."
    new "Vaelen's behavior ever since Bagrad had troubled her."

    old "He had always been a man who walked his own path and made the world bend to it, but he seemed even more eccentric than usual."
    new "He had always been a man who walked his own path and made the world bend to it, but he seemed even more eccentric than usual."

    old "Then there was also the matter of the stone."
    new "Then there was also the matter of the stone."

    old "A fate stone, the spirit had called it."
    new "A fate stone, the spirit had called it."

    old "She didn't see much of it, but she could see how Vaelen clutched the stone, underneath his clothing."
    new "She didn't see much of it, but she could see how Vaelen clutched the stone, underneath his clothing."

    old "Having obtained the thing, the thing now seemed to have obtained him."
    new "Having obtained the thing, the thing now seemed to have obtained him."

    old "And finally, there was the matter of the spirit's prophecy..."
    new "And finally, there was the matter of the spirit's prophecy..."

    old "Sarah was not one who gave much value to witchcraft of any kind, but the creature seemed too serious in how it had spoken."
    new "Sarah was not one who gave much value to witchcraft of any kind, but the creature seemed too serious in how it had spoken."

    old "Warnings of the future."
    new "Warnings of the future."

    old "Sarah shook her head, clearing her mind from the nonesense."
    new "Sarah shook her head, clearing her mind from the nonesense."

    old "She had enough troubles in her life as it was, she didn't need to spend more worrying about magics and spirits."
    new "She had enough troubles in her life as it was, she didn't need to spend more worrying about magics and spirits."

    old "Suddenly, the covering from the wagon parted and a figure emerged."
    new "Suddenly, the covering from the wagon parted and a figure emerged."

    old "You hanging in there?"
    new "You hanging in there?"

    old "Sarah looked out ahead over the road."
    new "Sarah looked out ahead over the road."

    old "She could trace the curves and bends by following how the carts and wagons ahead of her twisted and turned."
    new "She could trace the curves and bends by following how the carts and wagons ahead of her twisted and turned."

    old "It's only been a few hours since we've left."
    new "It's only been a few hours since we've left."

    old "Yeah, but still."
    new "Yeah, but still."

    old "Kate gestured towards the sky."
    new "Kate gestured towards the sky."

    old "Sarah didn't need to look where she was pointing to know that she was pointing at the sun."
    new "Sarah didn't need to look where she was pointing to know that she was pointing at the sun."

    old "The sun."
    new "The sun."

    old "It was an odd thing, Sarah had come to realize."
    new "It was an odd thing, Sarah had come to realize."

    old "All her life she'd known the sun was there, but only since coming to Bagrad had she become so intently aware of its existence."
    new "All her life she'd known the sun was there, but only since coming to Bagrad had she become so intently aware of its existence."

    old "Here, in the great deserts of Bagrad, the sun existed in its most intense state."
    new "Here, in the great deserts of Bagrad, the sun existed in its most intense state."

    old "It dominated the sky, punished anyone who so much as glanced at it, and weighed them down with a constant oppressive heat."
    new "It dominated the sky, punished anyone who so much as glanced at it, and weighed them down with a constant oppressive heat."

    old "When it fell beyond the horizon, it cast rays of light so violent to the eyes that one had to be careful not to be struck blind."
    new "When it fell beyond the horizon, it cast rays of light so violent to the eyes that one had to be careful not to be struck blind."

    old "And even when it fell over the horizon, dissapearing, it reminded everyone of its absence by withdrawing its heat altogether."
    new "And even when it fell over the horizon, dissapearing, it reminded everyone of its absence by withdrawing its heat altogether."

    old "Crushing heat. Freezing cold."
    new "Crushing heat. Freezing cold."

    old "Oceans of sand. Rotted out trees."
    new "Oceans of sand. Rotted out trees."

    old "Everything about this place, up from the sky, down to the land, seemed to tell the same story."
    new "Everything about this place, up from the sky, down to the land, seemed to tell the same story."

    old "This land is not made for humans."
    new "This land is not made for humans."

    old "My armor is fucking boiling me alive, I can tell you that much."
    new "My armor is fucking boiling me alive, I can tell you that much."

    old "Kate leaned in closer."
    new "Kate leaned in closer."

    old "I can help you take it off if you want."
    new "I can help you take it off if you want."

    old "You can't be serious."
    new "You can't be serious."

    old "You're thinking about that in this heat?"
    new "You're thinking about that in this heat?"

    old "What can I say, the idea of you undressed and covered in sweat isn't entirely unappealing."
    new "What can I say, the idea of you undressed and covered in sweat isn't entirely unappealing."

    old "Wouldn't be the first time."
    new "Wouldn't be the first time."

    old "Kate poked Sarah in her ribs."
    new "Kate poked Sarah in her ribs."

    old "You know, most of the men in the company think with their dicks, but you might be the only woman that does."
    new "You know, most of the men in the company think with their dicks, but you might be the only woman that does."

    old "Kate fell back into her seat."
    new "Kate fell back into her seat."

    old "Maybe. Or the only one whose honest about that."
    new "Maybe. Or the only one whose honest about that."

    old "In silence, the two rode next to each other for a while, suffering the torture of the sun together somehow seemed to make it more bearable."
    new "In silence, the two rode next to each other for a while, suffering the torture of the sun together somehow seemed to make it more bearable."

    old "The creaking of the wagon wheels droned as the convoy slowly crawled along the road."
    new "The creaking of the wagon wheels droned as the convoy slowly crawled along the road."

    old "Beyond each hill and each dune, the world offered up only a new horizon, appearing identical to the one before."
    new "Beyond each hill and each dune, the world offered up only a new horizon, appearing identical to the one before."

    old "The distance they were covering was about as much as Sarah could have hoped for, but she had already begun to worry."
    new "The distance they were covering was about as much as Sarah could have hoped for, but she had already begun to worry."

    old "The road out here was closest to Bagrad, closest to the center of what had once been the sprawling empire."
    new "The road out here was closest to Bagrad, closest to the center of what had once been the sprawling empire."

    old "Even these roads showed signs of decay from a lack of maintenance and being subjected to the elements of the desert."
    new "Even these roads showed signs of decay from a lack of maintenance and being subjected to the elements of the desert."

    old "The truth was that the fact that these roads remained after centuries was a testament to their stunning quality, but this was little comfort to those who lived in the present."
    new "The truth was that the fact that these roads remained after centuries was a testament to their stunning quality, but this was little comfort to those who lived in the present."

    old "One missing stone, causing a chip in the wheel, snapping an axle, it was all that it would take to bring a cart to a halt."
    new "One missing stone, causing a chip in the wheel, snapping an axle, it was all that it would take to bring a cart to a halt."

    old "Then they'd have to decide."
    new "Then they'd have to decide."

    old "Leave the cart be and waste time transfering the cargo from one to the other, or try to repair it, and risk bringing the whole convoy to a halt."
    new "Leave the cart be and waste time transfering the cargo from one to the other, or try to repair it, and risk bringing the whole convoy to a halt."

    old "Usually, out on the road, such repairs were a small matter."
    new "Usually, out on the road, such repairs were a small matter."

    old "Any broken cart could simply work to fix itself and catch up later, but out here, this wasn't an option."
    new "Any broken cart could simply work to fix itself and catch up later, but out here, this wasn't an option."

    old "Everybody in the mercenary company had to move as one, united into a single unit."
    new "Everybody in the mercenary company had to move as one, united into a single unit."

    old "They simply had no choice. Alone, nobody could hope to survive the desert."
    new "They simply had no choice. Alone, nobody could hope to survive the desert."

    old "And so the convoy crawled forward with care, seeking to avoid any disaster, while knowing that it would be impossible to stave off disaster forever in a place like this."
    new "And so the convoy crawled forward with care, seeking to avoid any disaster, while knowing that it would be impossible to stave off disaster forever in a place like this."

    old "So, Vaelen tell you what's what?"
    new "So, Vaelen tell you what's what?"

    old "He tells me about the same as any other."
    new "He tells me about the same as any other."

    old "Bullshit."
    new "Bullshit."

    old "Kate spoke the word like a whip."
    new "Kate spoke the word like a whip."

    old "Everybody knows you're his golden girl. If he'd tell anybody, it's you."
    new "Everybody knows you're his golden girl. If he'd tell anybody, it's you."

    old "He told me it's about going to a town called Nauyziri, but you know that too."
    new "He told me it's about going to a town called Nauyziri, but you know that too."

    old "But he didn't tell you why? I mean...fuck...there ain't nothing out there."
    new "But he didn't tell you why? I mean...fuck...there ain't nothing out there."

    old "You're free to turn around."
    new "You're free to turn around."

    old "I'd rather die out there with you than die by myself trying to get back."
    new "I'd rather die out there with you than die by myself trying to get back."

    old "Not to mention, I don't wanna see what Bagrad is going to turn into over the next few days."
    new "Not to mention, I don't wanna see what Bagrad is going to turn into over the next few days."

    old "Sarah knew what Kate meant."
    new "Sarah knew what Kate meant."

    old "Preparing for their expedition, the mercenary company had squeezed the very last of the resources from the city."
    new "Preparing for their expedition, the mercenary company had squeezed the very last of the resources from the city."

    old "Where before they had been undersupplied, now the city bordered on starvation."
    new "Where before they had been undersupplied, now the city bordered on starvation."

    old "Soon the people would begin to starve."
    new "Soon the people would begin to starve."

    old "Sarah hated that she'd seen that too over the years. A city under siege, its people so starved you could count their ribs."
    new "Sarah hated that she'd seen that too over the years. A city under siege, its people so starved you could count their ribs."

    old "She'd surprised herself over the years, learning just how much she could take."
    new "She'd surprised herself over the years, learning just how much she could take."

    old "She'd also scared herself, realizing there might not be a limit to what she could endure."
    new "She'd also scared herself, realizing there might not be a limit to what she could endure."

    old "Well, like I said, I don't know a damn thing more than you do."
    new "Well, like I said, I don't know a damn thing more than you do."

    old "And that's fine with you?"
    new "And that's fine with you?"

    old "You don't mind riding further out than any soul should, all because Vaelen ordered us too?"
    new "You don't mind riding further out than any soul should, all because Vaelen ordered us too?"

    old "What do you want me to do about it? You know how he gets when he has these ideas..."
    new "What do you want me to do about it? You know how he gets when he has these ideas..."

    old "Besides, if you don't trust him, go take it up with him."
    new "Besides, if you don't trust him, go take it up with him."

    old "Nah, I trust him. And fuck it, even if I didn't trust him, I'd throw my life away for him too if he asked."
    new "Nah, I trust him. And fuck it, even if I didn't trust him, I'd throw my life away for him too if he asked."

    old "You don't mean that."
    new "You don't mean that."

    old "Yeah, I do. Never met any person in the world that I can say that about."
    new "Yeah, I do. Never met any person in the world that I can say that about."

    old "Kate paused for a brief moment."
    new "Kate paused for a brief moment."

    old "And maybe you too."
    new "And maybe you too."

    old "This world is filled to the brim with worthless people. Best we can do is try and look out for the handful of people that matter."
    new "This world is filled to the brim with worthless people. Best we can do is try and look out for the handful of people that matter."

    old "Sarah looked out towards the horizon, the sun had begun its descent. A few hours and the scorching heat would turn to biting cold."
    new "Sarah looked out towards the horizon, the sun had begun its descent. A few hours and the scorching heat would turn to biting cold."

    old "Do you really think that?"
    new "Do you really think that?"

    old "Kate nodded while looking away from her."
    new "Kate nodded while looking away from her."

    old "Yeah, I don't like most people."
    new "Yeah, I don't like most people."

    old "Maybe you should give them a chance, not everybody is that bad."
    new "Maybe you should give them a chance, not everybody is that bad."

    old "Easy for you to say, you grew up in a castle. People are nice to you if you live in a castle."
    new "Easy for you to say, you grew up in a castle. People are nice to you if you live in a castle."

    old "People smile, and say please, and do whatever you ask them."
    new "People smile, and say please, and do whatever you ask them."

    old "I remember almost starving, sitting in an alley, and still nobody would offer me a fucking piece of bread for free."
    new "I remember almost starving, sitting in an alley, and still nobody would offer me a fucking piece of bread for free."

    old "Kate leaned forward, brushing away the sweat laced hair from her face."
    new "Kate leaned forward, brushing away the sweat laced hair from her face."

    old "You think the real world is people being nice and smiling."
    new "You think the real world is people being nice and smiling."

    old "Well I've seen men trying to buy me for a night in exchange for some food and something to drink."
    new "Well I've seen men trying to buy me for a night in exchange for some food and something to drink."

    old "Then the next day, I see them walking down the streets with their families, wife and kids and everything, going to pray."
    new "Then the next day, I see them walking down the streets with their families, wife and kids and everything, going to pray."

    old "Kate spat besides the wagon as it rolled on."
    new "Kate spat besides the wagon as it rolled on."

    old "Most of the world is just people putting up fronts."
    new "Most of the world is just people putting up fronts."

    old "You're a cynic."
    new "You're a cynic."

    old "Well, if I am, the fucking world made me one."
    new "Well, if I am, the fucking world made me one."

    old "If I'm going to give up my life for anyone, it's going to be for the handful of people that are worth it. Maybe they can make this world a slightly better place."
    new "If I'm going to give up my life for anyone, it's going to be for the handful of people that are worth it. Maybe they can make this world a slightly better place."

    old "The rest of it? Let it crumble like the monuments they build out here."
    new "The rest of it? Let it crumble like the monuments they build out here."

    old "Kate looked out across the horizon."
    new "Kate looked out across the horizon."

    old "You ever wonder how many slaves they worked to death, just to build these things?"
    new "You ever wonder how many slaves they worked to death, just to build these things?"

    old "Sarah didn't want to think about it, nor could she answer Kate, so instead she simply said nothing."
    new "Sarah didn't want to think about it, nor could she answer Kate, so instead she simply said nothing."

    old "As the sun slowly descended from the sky, falling past and over the horizon, the world turned dark in what seemed like only minutes."
    new "As the sun slowly descended from the sky, falling past and over the horizon, the world turned dark in what seemed like only minutes."

    old "The heat withdrew rapidly, replaced only be a cold that seemed equally discomforting."
    new "The heat withdrew rapidly, replaced only be a cold that seemed equally discomforting."

    old "Ahead, Sarah watched as the wagons began to pull away from the road, starting the formation of a camp."
    new "Ahead, Sarah watched as the wagons began to pull away from the road, starting the formation of a camp."

    old "I have to go help my men a few carts up ahead, but I'll see about finding you later."
    new "I have to go help my men a few carts up ahead, but I'll see about finding you later."

    old "Kate leapt from the cart and walked out into the growing cluster and chaos of people now setting up camp."
    new "Kate leapt from the cart and walked out into the growing cluster and chaos of people now setting up camp."

    old "Above her, Sarah could see the stars growing brighter with each passing moment."
    new "Above her, Sarah could see the stars growing brighter with each passing moment."

    old "She found herself wondering if they had ever looked so bright before in her life."
    new "She found herself wondering if they had ever looked so bright before in her life."

    old "It wasn't long before the first glowing embers of newly lit campfires could be seen."
    new "It wasn't long before the first glowing embers of newly lit campfires could be seen."

    old "All across the quickly growing camp, the small pockets of fire drew in soldiers, gathered together for comfort and safety."
    new "All across the quickly growing camp, the small pockets of fire drew in soldiers, gathered together for comfort and safety."

    old "Sarah left the cart and joined one of the fires nearby."
    new "Sarah left the cart and joined one of the fires nearby."

    old "Before walking towards the campfire, Sarah turned around to the cart."
    new "Before walking towards the campfire, Sarah turned around to the cart."

    old "You can come out if you want, stretch your legs."
    new "You can come out if you want, stretch your legs."

    old "Slowly, like a rabbit emerging from its hiding place, Samayra emerged."
    new "Slowly, like a rabbit emerging from its hiding place, Samayra emerged."

    old "At first only her head stuck out from the wagon, but once confident it was safe, she leapt down into the sand with a dancer's grace."
    new "At first only her head stuck out from the wagon, but once confident it was safe, she leapt down into the sand with a dancer's grace."

    old "Are you sure it's alright?"
    new "Are you sure it's alright?"

    old "Don't worry, you're here under my protection. Nobody will bother you."
    new "Don't worry, you're here under my protection. Nobody will bother you."

    old "Samayra quickly crossed the distance between them, following closely behind Sarah."
    new "Samayra quickly crossed the distance between them, following closely behind Sarah."

    old "Sarah sat down by the campfire."
    new "Sarah sat down by the campfire."

    old "Samayra joined her."
    new "Samayra joined her."

    old "She put her sword down besides her."
    new "She put her sword down besides her."

    old "Across the campfire, she could see the faces of the other soldiers."
    new "Across the campfire, she could see the faces of the other soldiers."

    old "Some she knew, some she didn't."
    new "Some she knew, some she didn't."

    old "Each gave a small nod of acknowledgement, a recognition of her rank in the mercenary company, but not much more than that."
    new "Each gave a small nod of acknowledgement, a recognition of her rank in the mercenary company, but not much more than that."

    old "Sarah found that as a commander, most were either too scared to interact with her or too eager, each could be off putting in its own way."
    new "Sarah found that as a commander, most were either too scared to interact with her or too eager, each could be off putting in its own way."

    old "Samayra sat next to her, nearly close enough to sit shoulder to shoulder."
    new "Samayra sat next to her, nearly close enough to sit shoulder to shoulder."

    old "How did you manage with the heat? I hope it wasn't too bad."
    new "How did you manage with the heat? I hope it wasn't too bad."

    old "Samayra shrugged."
    new "Samayra shrugged."

    old "I don't really think this is too bad."
    new "I don't really think this is too bad."

    old "Really? I'm almost boiling in this armor, yet without it, it almost feels worse."
    new "Really? I'm almost boiling in this armor, yet without it, it almost feels worse."

    old "Samayra laughed."
    new "Samayra laughed."

    old "Maybe you're the one who's out of place here."
    new "Maybe you're the one who's out of place here."

    old "I've never known a different climate than this."
    new "I've never known a different climate than this."

    old "Sarah hadn't realized that yet."
    new "Sarah hadn't realized that yet."

    old "She knew the palace had been all that Samayra had ever known, but she hadn't yet concluded that this meant the desert and its violent elements appeared natural to her."
    new "She knew the palace had been all that Samayra had ever known, but she hadn't yet concluded that this meant the desert and its violent elements appeared natural to her."

    old "Huh, I hadn't thought about that."
    new "Huh, I hadn't thought about that."

    old "It's different, isn't it? The weather, I mean, in places like Rosanna?"
    new "It's different, isn't it? The weather, I mean, in places like Rosanna?"

    old "You get all sorts. Warm days, cold days, rainy days. Snow even, in the winter months."
    new "You get all sorts. Warm days, cold days, rainy days. Snow even, in the winter months."

    old "Samayra's face suddenly lighted up."
    new "Samayra's face suddenly lighted up."

    old "Snow?! Really?!"
    new "Snow?! Really?!"

    old "Wow, I only ever read about that in books. Does it really just...cover up the whole land?"
    new "Wow, I only ever read about that in books. Does it really just...cover up the whole land?"

    old "Yeah, on a good day it's no different than all the sand you can see here, just a whole world covered in white."
    new "Yeah, on a good day it's no different than all the sand you can see here, just a whole world covered in white."

    old "Sarah could see Samayra's eyes grow wider."
    new "Sarah could see Samayra's eyes grow wider."

    old "You're lying! There can't possibly be that much!"
    new "You're lying! There can't possibly be that much!"

    old "I swear."
    new "I swear."

    old "When we get back to Lethram, maybe you'll actually see some."
    new "When we get back to Lethram, maybe you'll actually see some."

    old "Samayra's eyes drifted away, seemingly lost in a fantasy."
    new "Samayra's eyes drifted away, seemingly lost in a fantasy."

    old "Sarah sat alone with her thoughts as the other soldiers around her began to eat and drink, the mood slowly growing more festive with each round."
    new "Sarah sat alone with her thoughts as the other soldiers around her began to eat and drink, the mood slowly growing more festive with each round."

    old "They had conquered a great city, were rich on loot. They had a reason for being in good spirits."
    new "They had conquered a great city, were rich on loot. They had a reason for being in good spirits."

    old "One of the soldiers raised up a glass and a woman emerged from the shadows."
    new "One of the soldiers raised up a glass and a woman emerged from the shadows."

    old "Clothed in little if anything at all, she carried a pitcher and poured beer into the man's cup."
    new "Clothed in little if anything at all, she carried a pitcher and poured beer into the man's cup."

    old "For her efforts, she received some jeers and groping of her body as she went around the campfire, refilling the cups."
    new "For her efforts, she received some jeers and groping of her body as she went around the campfire, refilling the cups."

    old "When she passed by Sarah, she offered to refill her cup as well."
    new "When she passed by Sarah, she offered to refill her cup as well."

    old "Sarah looked into the woman's eyes."
    new "Sarah looked into the woman's eyes."

    old "Hollowed out."
    new "Hollowed out."

    old "Whatever spark resided in a person's eyes, hers had been snuffed out."
    new "Whatever spark resided in a person's eyes, hers had been snuffed out."

    old "The woman continued and passed by her."
    new "The woman continued and passed by her."

    old "Her skin colour and fashion of dress told Sarah enough. This woman was one of the many citizens of Bagrad that had been made a slave."
    new "Her skin colour and fashion of dress told Sarah enough. This woman was one of the many citizens of Bagrad that had been made a slave."

    old "Slavery wasn't legal in Lethram, but this far out from any civilization, it didn't seem to matter."
    new "Slavery wasn't legal in Lethram, but this far out from any civilization, it didn't seem to matter."

    old "The Mythran army made no objection of slavery, given that it was the law-of-the-land back in Mythra, and so nobody stopped the mercenary company from taking their own slaves."
    new "The Mythran army made no objection of slavery, given that it was the law-of-the-land back in Mythra, and so nobody stopped the mercenary company from taking their own slaves."

    old "Perhaps they'd have to be released before they returned to Lethram, but Sarah could see most were content if only to own slaves for the moment."
    new "Perhaps they'd have to be released before they returned to Lethram, but Sarah could see most were content if only to own slaves for the moment."

    old "She could see their ravenous eyes, roaming freely across the woman's body, knowing each of them could and likely would possess her."
    new "She could see their ravenous eyes, roaming freely across the woman's body, knowing each of them could and likely would possess her."

    old "It troubled her more than it did them."
    new "It troubled her more than it did them."

    old "A part of her could never forget that, if not for Kate's intervention, she herself would have been captured and likely treated no different than this woman."
    new "A part of her could never forget that, if not for Kate's intervention, she herself would have been captured and likely treated no different than this woman."

